1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,361
We're in the very far future.

2
00:00:02,481 --> 00:00:03,521
RYAN: Seven humans left.

3
00:00:03,641 --> 00:00:04,961
Cyberdrones.

4
00:00:05,081 --> 00:00:07,121
(SCREAMING)

5
00:00:07,241 --> 00:00:08,161
No!

6
00:00:08,281 --> 00:00:10,321
Go with the humans. Help them.
Get them out of here.

7
00:00:10,441 --> 00:00:12,761
You won't make it
back to the TARDIS alive.

8
00:00:14,081 --> 00:00:15,881
We know where you are.

9
00:00:16,001 --> 00:00:17,681
We will find you.

10
00:00:17,801 --> 00:00:20,081
The Boundary - it's where
we've been trying to get to.

11
00:00:20,201 --> 00:00:21,161
A gateway, a direct route

12
00:00:21,281 --> 00:00:23,001
out of here
into another random part

13
00:00:23,121 --> 00:00:23,961
of the universe.

14
00:00:24,081 --> 00:00:26,881
Whoa! Wow!

15
00:00:27,001 --> 00:00:28,161
Be afraid, Doctor,

16
00:00:28,281 --> 00:00:30,961
because everything
is about to change.

17
00:01:05,201 --> 00:01:06,441
DOCTOR: How are you here?

18
00:01:06,561 --> 00:01:08,161
MASTER: Take my hand.

19
00:01:08,281 --> 00:01:09,721
Never.

20
00:01:09,841 --> 00:01:11,361
Take my hand

21
00:01:11,481 --> 00:01:14,881
or I turn them into
tiny human dolls right here.

22
00:01:15,001 --> 00:01:17,761
How have you connected
Gallifrey to that Boundary?

23
00:01:17,881 --> 00:01:21,521
Fine. You really want me
to show you I'm serious?

24
00:01:21,641 --> 00:01:23,921
Eenie, meenie, miney...

25
00:01:24,041 --> 00:01:26,001
Miney.

26
00:01:26,121 --> 00:01:29,961
Fine, I'll play your game.

27
00:01:30,081 --> 00:01:33,081
- I'll be back.
- She won't.

28
00:01:33,201 --> 00:01:34,801
And it's not a game.

29
00:01:34,921 --> 00:01:36,521
Good luck, humans.

30
00:01:38,401 --> 00:01:40,121
RYAN: We have to go
through there.

31
00:01:40,241 --> 00:01:41,601
- We have to go and get her.
- No,

32
00:01:41,721 --> 00:01:42,801
we have to wait for the others.

33
00:01:42,921 --> 00:01:45,361
(RUMBLING)

34
00:01:50,801 --> 00:01:53,001
They're here.

35
00:01:54,641 --> 00:01:56,321
(BESCOT GRUNTS)

36
00:01:56,441 --> 00:01:58,841
- Over here!
- Go, go, go, go!

37
00:02:00,281 --> 00:02:02,161
BESCOT: I'll cover you!

38
00:02:07,881 --> 00:02:09,841
Come on! Bescot!

39
00:02:09,961 --> 00:02:11,001
Argh!

40
00:02:13,601 --> 00:02:14,801
No!

41
00:02:23,761 --> 00:02:25,321
The ship is ours.

42
00:02:29,481 --> 00:02:33,481
Look upon my work, Doctor,
and despair.

43
00:02:37,801 --> 00:02:40,161
Remember how we used to run
through those streets

44
00:02:40,281 --> 00:02:42,001
as children?

45
00:02:42,121 --> 00:02:44,441
The alleys where we'd hide
from Borusa

46
00:02:44,561 --> 00:02:46,001
as we skipped classes?

47
00:02:48,401 --> 00:02:49,401
All gone now.

48
00:02:51,201 --> 00:02:54,281
Come on,
ask me why I did this.

49
00:02:57,201 --> 00:02:58,401
Why did you do this?

50
00:02:58,521 --> 00:03:01,001
Not telling you. (LAUGHS)

51
00:03:02,081 --> 00:03:03,001
Oh, crack a smile.

52
00:03:03,121 --> 00:03:04,761
- Proud of yourself?
- Definitely.

53
00:03:04,881 --> 00:03:07,281
All this death -
finally made you happy?

54
00:03:07,401 --> 00:03:08,201
Ecstatic.

55
00:03:08,321 --> 00:03:10,641
And has it calmed all the rage?

56
00:03:14,601 --> 00:03:17,081
I don't think
anything will ever do that.

57
00:03:20,161 --> 00:03:22,881
We're going to take a tour
through the capital,

58
00:03:23,001 --> 00:03:25,561
or its ruins, at least.

59
00:03:25,681 --> 00:03:27,481
Things I need to show you.

60
00:03:27,601 --> 00:03:31,681
And, um, I know you're worried
about your friends.

61
00:03:33,161 --> 00:03:35,241
Plotting how to get away.
I can see it in your eyes.

62
00:03:36,761 --> 00:03:38,721
But you can't help them,

63
00:03:38,841 --> 00:03:40,441
so don't even think about it.

64
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:46,881
Down you come. That's it.
Yaz, come on.

65
00:03:48,201 --> 00:03:49,361
Where's Bescot?

66
00:03:49,481 --> 00:03:50,881
They killed her.
We have to go back for her.

67
00:03:51,001 --> 00:03:52,241
No, no, no.
No, you can't do that, mate.

68
00:03:52,361 --> 00:03:53,801
Listen, don't tell me
what I can't do.

69
00:03:55,081 --> 00:03:57,241
She had nightmares

70
00:03:57,361 --> 00:03:59,681
about being captured
and converted.

71
00:03:59,801 --> 00:04:01,081
I can't let that happen.

72
00:04:01,201 --> 00:04:02,761
Do you really think
that she would want you

73
00:04:02,881 --> 00:04:04,161
to go back there
and risk your life?

74
00:04:04,281 --> 00:04:06,441
I owe her. And what difference
does it make anyway?

75
00:04:06,561 --> 00:04:07,961
We don't stand a chance here.

76
00:04:08,081 --> 00:04:10,321
We are stuck on a ship
stacked with Cybermen.

77
00:04:10,441 --> 00:04:11,361
Four humans sticking out

78
00:04:11,481 --> 00:04:13,041
on every surveillance system
they've got.

79
00:04:13,161 --> 00:04:14,081
He's right,

80
00:04:14,201 --> 00:04:15,801
and I've been thinking
about that. I've got an idea.

81
00:04:15,921 --> 00:04:17,361
It's a bit of a mad one -
quite dangerous

82
00:04:17,481 --> 00:04:18,521
and it might not work -

83
00:04:18,641 --> 00:04:21,081
but we've got form with plans
like that, ain't we, Yaz?

84
00:04:21,201 --> 00:04:23,721
Yeah, our speciality.

85
00:04:25,481 --> 00:04:26,681
How dangerous?

86
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:36,081
GRAHAM: We use their arm our

87
00:04:36,201 --> 00:04:37,441
so they don't notice us.

88
00:04:37,561 --> 00:04:39,841
That way, we can move around
and get off the ship.

89
00:04:39,961 --> 00:04:42,841
So you want us to disguise
ourselves as Cybermen?

90
00:04:42,961 --> 00:04:44,081
Have you ever opened one up?

91
00:04:44,201 --> 00:04:45,321
Well, I guess
it won't be pleasant.

92
00:04:45,441 --> 00:04:46,761
They're full of human remains.

93
00:04:46,881 --> 00:04:48,401
Well, I don't need it
spelling out, do I?

94
00:04:48,521 --> 00:04:51,761
You can't fake being a Cyberman
for any length of time.

95
00:04:51,881 --> 00:04:53,521
We only need to do it
for long enough

96
00:04:53,641 --> 00:04:54,681
to get us out of here.

97
00:04:57,121 --> 00:05:00,361
If you do the bodies,
I could disable

98
00:05:00,481 --> 00:05:02,441
the suit connection
into the shared neural network.

99
00:05:02,561 --> 00:05:03,841
It's insane.

100
00:05:03,961 --> 00:05:06,321
Well, I didn't say it was
a perfect plan, did I?

101
00:05:06,441 --> 00:05:08,321
But it is
the best one we've got.

102
00:05:16,041 --> 00:05:18,521
This is my weapon store.

103
00:05:20,081 --> 00:05:21,281
This all you got?

104
00:05:21,401 --> 00:05:22,521
Well, it's quite hard

105
00:05:22,641 --> 00:05:24,281
to get deliveries out here,
you know.

106
00:05:24,401 --> 00:05:28,481
I had hoped I'd fought
my last battle a long time ago.

107
00:05:28,601 --> 00:05:30,201
Still... (CHUCKLES)

108
00:05:32,441 --> 00:05:34,321
This old general
still knows a few tricks.

109
00:05:34,441 --> 00:05:35,921
I'm not too sure about weapons.

110
00:05:36,041 --> 00:05:38,561
Yeah, well,
I'm sure about Cybermen.

111
00:05:38,681 --> 00:05:40,681
Now, you fight them or you die.

112
00:05:40,801 --> 00:05:43,681
They don't have any mercy.

113
00:05:43,801 --> 00:05:49,001
You can be a pacifist tomorrow.
Today, you have to survive.

114
00:05:53,761 --> 00:05:55,001
MASTER: Ah!

115
00:05:55,121 --> 00:05:57,721
The Citadel,
the heart of Gallifrey.

116
00:05:57,841 --> 00:06:00,121
Recognise the old place?

117
00:06:00,241 --> 00:06:02,521
I was thinking
I might knock through there,

118
00:06:02,641 --> 00:06:04,761
put a wet room there,

119
00:06:04,881 --> 00:06:07,521
screening room there.
(CHUCKLES)

120
00:06:07,641 --> 00:06:10,121
Torture room in the cellar,
naturally.

121
00:06:11,441 --> 00:06:13,001
Oh.

122
00:06:13,121 --> 00:06:14,721
And see through there?

123
00:06:14,841 --> 00:06:17,401
The Panopticon.

124
00:06:17,521 --> 00:06:19,561
Well, what's left, which, uh...

125
00:06:19,681 --> 00:06:21,641
...which isn't much.

126
00:06:25,961 --> 00:06:29,361
We had some fun there,
didn't we, eh?

127
00:06:32,601 --> 00:06:33,601
Graduated.

128
00:06:35,761 --> 00:06:37,761
Assassinated presidents.

129
00:06:37,881 --> 00:06:39,161
(GIGGLES)

130
00:06:39,281 --> 00:06:41,401
The best of times!

131
00:06:41,521 --> 00:06:45,041
But I thought here would be
a fitting place to end this.

132
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:47,161
(CHIMES)

133
00:06:47,281 --> 00:06:50,001
Oh. Oop. Excuse me.

134
00:06:50,121 --> 00:06:51,561
Check my notifications.

135
00:06:53,281 --> 00:06:55,201
(BEEPS)

136
00:06:55,321 --> 00:06:57,321
Oh, goo die!

137
00:06:57,441 --> 00:07:00,721
The Cybermen are here,
at the Boundary.

138
00:07:00,841 --> 00:07:03,241
Better extend
the hand of friendship.

139
00:07:03,361 --> 00:07:05,281
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

140
00:07:05,401 --> 00:07:08,281
Breaker 1-2 calling all Cybes.

141
00:07:08,401 --> 00:07:10,321
Calling all Cybes.

142
00:07:10,441 --> 00:07:11,681
CYBERGUARD: Leader,

143
00:07:11,801 --> 00:07:15,361
incoming holo-transmission
from beyond the Boundary.

144
00:07:15,481 --> 00:07:16,841
(EXHALES EXCITEDLY)

145
00:07:16,961 --> 00:07:18,961
Hello, Cybercarrier!

146
00:07:19,081 --> 00:07:20,641
Ooh, you look rough.

147
00:07:20,761 --> 00:07:22,081
Or is that a choice?

148
00:07:23,681 --> 00:07:25,121
Don't mean
to conversion-shame you.

149
00:07:25,241 --> 00:07:26,241
(CLEARS THROAT)

150
00:07:26,361 --> 00:07:28,081
Who are you?

151
00:07:28,201 --> 00:07:30,841
You may call me Master.

152
00:07:32,561 --> 00:07:35,601
I want you to think of me
as your new best friend.

153
00:07:35,721 --> 00:07:37,001
Now,

154
00:07:37,121 --> 00:07:40,041
the Boundary between worlds,
this...

155
00:07:40,161 --> 00:07:43,121
...beautiful anomalous fluke -

156
00:07:43,241 --> 00:07:45,161
come through it.

157
00:07:45,281 --> 00:07:47,161
Join me.

158
00:07:47,281 --> 00:07:49,801
Why would we join you?

159
00:07:49,921 --> 00:07:53,041
Because I have a planet
going spare right here.

160
00:07:54,641 --> 00:07:58,041
The planet formerly known
as Gallifrey.

161
00:07:58,161 --> 00:08:01,361
No. Don't bring them here.
This is between you and me.

162
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:03,801
(BUZZES)

163
00:08:03,921 --> 00:08:05,161
Don't heckle, dear.

164
00:08:06,641 --> 00:08:09,481
I can always decide
to cut you short.

165
00:08:11,881 --> 00:08:14,161
I promise
I'll roll out the red carpet.

166
00:08:14,281 --> 00:08:17,601
It's red because it's drenched
in the blood of our people.

167
00:08:17,721 --> 00:08:19,041
(GIGGLES)

168
00:08:22,321 --> 00:08:24,641
I've sent you
the navigation patterns.

169
00:08:24,761 --> 00:08:26,721
Come right to the hearts.

170
00:08:26,841 --> 00:08:29,601
Do what so many
of your predecessors

171
00:08:29,721 --> 00:08:31,241
fantasised about...

172
00:08:32,481 --> 00:08:37,201
Land your ship
in the ruins of Gallifrey.

173
00:08:38,681 --> 00:08:39,601
On the way through,

174
00:08:39,721 --> 00:08:41,001
you should send
a death squadron.

175
00:08:41,121 --> 00:08:42,841
Do you call it
a death squadron?

176
00:08:42,961 --> 00:08:44,841
A deletion squad.

177
00:08:44,961 --> 00:08:46,721
No, a recruitment patrol,

178
00:08:46,841 --> 00:08:48,801
a human-juicing party,

179
00:08:48,921 --> 00:08:52,481
to eliminate the three humans
left alive on that planet.

180
00:08:52,601 --> 00:08:55,001
They're weak.

181
00:08:55,121 --> 00:08:56,761
It shouldn't take much.

182
00:08:59,161 --> 00:09:00,961
See you in a bit.

183
00:09:04,241 --> 00:09:07,921
Send three execution units
to the surface.

184
00:09:11,761 --> 00:09:14,161
And set course for Gallifrey.

185
00:09:25,361 --> 00:09:27,321
KO SHARMUS ON COMMS:
Here they come.

186
00:09:27,441 --> 00:09:29,121
Gird your loins, gentlemen.

187
00:09:29,241 --> 00:09:30,921
Uh... I don't...

188
00:09:31,041 --> 00:09:33,321
- I don't how to do that.
- Me neither.

189
00:09:45,081 --> 00:09:46,401
RAVIO: Transmat.

190
00:09:48,241 --> 00:09:51,401
KO SHARMUS: As my first
commanding officer used to say,

191
00:09:51,521 --> 00:09:52,521
"Be brave.

192
00:09:52,641 --> 00:09:54,441
"Be swift

193
00:09:54,561 --> 00:09:58,321
"Most of all, be lucky."

194
00:10:00,161 --> 00:10:02,201
(ELECTRIC ZAPPING AND DRILLING)

195
00:10:07,441 --> 00:10:10,161
(DRILLING CONTINUES)

196
00:10:10,281 --> 00:10:11,961
All right?

197
00:10:12,081 --> 00:10:14,361
Yeah, yeah. You?

198
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:15,481
Yeah.

199
00:10:19,401 --> 00:10:21,481
Listen, Yaz, um...

200
00:10:23,281 --> 00:10:24,721
If we don't get out of this...

201
00:10:24,841 --> 00:10:26,961
- We will get out of this.
- Yeah, well...

202
00:10:27,081 --> 00:10:30,361
I know, but I'm just saying,
if we don't...

203
00:10:31,641 --> 00:10:33,481
...] want you to know I...

204
00:10:34,961 --> 00:10:38,081
I think you're
such an impressive young woman.

205
00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:41,521
Never thrown by anything.

206
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:43,601
Always fighting.

207
00:10:44,961 --> 00:10:46,201
Thanks.

208
00:10:46,321 --> 00:10:48,801
You said to the Doc
that you thought

209
00:10:48,921 --> 00:10:50,721
she was the best person
you'd ever met.

210
00:10:52,361 --> 00:10:53,561
You know what, Yaz?

211
00:10:54,921 --> 00:10:55,921
I think you are.

212
00:10:59,681 --> 00:11:02,921
You ain't got a time machine
or a sonic...

213
00:11:04,961 --> 00:11:06,521
...but you're never afraid

214
00:11:06,641 --> 00:11:07,881
and you're never beaten.

215
00:11:10,761 --> 00:11:12,281
I'm going to sound like a...

216
00:11:12,401 --> 00:11:13,961
...like a proper old man,

217
00:11:14,081 --> 00:11:15,521
but you're doing
your family proud, Yaz,

218
00:11:15,641 --> 00:11:17,081
you really are.

219
00:11:17,201 --> 00:11:19,361
In fact, you're doing
the whole human race proud.

220
00:11:24,681 --> 00:11:26,841
S-Sorry.
I haven't offended you, have I?

221
00:11:29,561 --> 00:11:32,681
It's the nicest thing
anyone's ever said to me.

222
00:11:32,801 --> 00:11:34,801
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

223
00:11:38,281 --> 00:11:40,801
You're not such a bad human
yourself either.

224
00:11:47,561 --> 00:11:49,041
(INDIGNANT) Not su...?

225
00:11:49,161 --> 00:11:50,521
Is that it?

226
00:11:52,401 --> 00:11:55,001
I've just said all them
lovely things about you,

227
00:11:55,121 --> 00:11:58,441
and all you give me is,
"You're not such a bad human"?

228
00:11:58,561 --> 00:12:00,361
Mate, I'm from Yorkshire -

229
00:12:00,481 --> 00:12:02,081
that's a love letter.

230
00:12:03,321 --> 00:12:05,161
We're ready.

231
00:12:05,281 --> 00:12:06,961
GRAHAM: Oh, OK.

232
00:12:16,441 --> 00:12:18,041
(GRUNTS)

233
00:12:22,001 --> 00:12:23,241
(RAPID BEEPING)

234
00:12:23,361 --> 00:12:25,641
Leader, unit malfunction

235
00:12:25,761 --> 00:12:28,961
in deep storage vault
Micron-Alpha.

236
00:12:32,361 --> 00:12:34,001
Show surveillance.

237
00:12:34,121 --> 00:12:37,961
Surveillance unavailable,
Leader.

238
00:12:38,081 --> 00:12:41,361
- The humans.
- Shall I activate a unit?

239
00:12:41,481 --> 00:12:44,321
No. They are mine.

240
00:12:48,281 --> 00:12:50,761
Why would you give Gallifrey
to the Cybermen?

241
00:12:50,881 --> 00:12:51,841
You're about to have

242
00:12:51,961 --> 00:12:53,561
much bigger things
to think about.

243
00:12:53,681 --> 00:12:55,041
I told you before

244
00:12:55,161 --> 00:12:57,521
that everything you knew
was a lie.

245
00:12:57,641 --> 00:13:00,201
Well, now you get
to face the truth,

246
00:13:00,321 --> 00:13:01,921
with me at your side.

247
00:13:02,041 --> 00:13:03,321
Do you really think
I'm going to believe

248
00:13:03,441 --> 00:13:04,841
anything that comes
out of your mouth?

249
00:13:05,921 --> 00:13:07,721
Do you remember this place,
Doctor?

250
00:13:11,681 --> 00:13:13,841
Next to the Panopticon,

251
00:13:13,961 --> 00:13:15,641
the Chamber of the Matrix,

252
00:13:15,761 --> 00:13:19,921
the Repository
of all Time Lord knowledge,

253
00:13:20,041 --> 00:13:23,401
a data bank of
every Time Lord consciousness,

254
00:13:23,521 --> 00:13:25,841
living and dead.

255
00:13:25,961 --> 00:13:29,121
Every experience
and every memory.

256
00:13:29,241 --> 00:13:32,441
The lived history of our race.

257
00:13:32,561 --> 00:13:34,881
I...I destroyed a lot
of things, but not this...

258
00:13:35,001 --> 00:13:36,961
...trove of secrets.

259
00:13:40,641 --> 00:13:42,361
This is what started it all.

260
00:13:42,481 --> 00:13:44,641
I-T was just playing,

261
00:13:44,761 --> 00:13:45,801
hacking the system.

262
00:13:45,921 --> 00:13:47,761
(STAMMERS)
I-I got lost in there.

263
00:13:47,881 --> 00:13:52,241
And then I found everything.

264
00:13:52,361 --> 00:13:54,121
Ah!

265
00:13:54,241 --> 00:13:56,521
Truth and reconciliation time,
Doctor.

266
00:13:56,641 --> 00:13:58,921
Well, maybe not reconciliation.

267
00:13:59,921 --> 00:14:02,281
But time you saw the truth
for yourself.

268
00:14:02,401 --> 00:14:04,161
What truth?

269
00:14:04,281 --> 00:14:06,321
(YELPS)

270
00:14:06,441 --> 00:14:08,001
(LAUGHS MANIACALLY)

271
00:14:08,121 --> 00:14:09,681
Paralysis field.

272
00:14:09,801 --> 00:14:12,161
- (GROANS)
- (LAUGHS)

273
00:14:12,281 --> 00:14:13,721
Whatever you want with me...

274
00:14:15,241 --> 00:14:16,881
...fine.

275
00:14:17,001 --> 00:14:18,321
But save my friends.

276
00:14:19,361 --> 00:14:21,361
Don't let the Cybermen
take them.

277
00:14:22,481 --> 00:14:24,921
If the history between us
means anything to you...

278
00:14:25,041 --> 00:14:28,161
I do believe you're appealing
to my better nature.

279
00:14:28,281 --> 00:14:30,081
And we both know
I don't have one.

280
00:14:30,201 --> 00:14:33,081
I'm not going to help them,
and neither are you.

281
00:14:34,881 --> 00:14:37,321
And the history between us
does mean something.

282
00:14:39,361 --> 00:14:42,441
It's the rage and pain
in my hearts.

283
00:14:45,081 --> 00:14:47,161
I'm sending you
deep into the Matrix

284
00:14:47,281 --> 00:14:49,041
to understand the truth...

285
00:14:50,401 --> 00:14:52,241
...of Gallifrey

286
00:14:52,361 --> 00:14:54,441
and of the Time Lords.

287
00:14:57,201 --> 00:14:58,241
Brace yourself.

288
00:15:00,721 --> 00:15:02,201
This is going to hurt.

289
00:15:15,521 --> 00:15:17,681
(MUFFLED BREATHING)

290
00:15:30,441 --> 00:15:33,801
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS)

291
00:15:43,921 --> 00:15:45,681
(SNIFFS)

292
00:15:51,641 --> 00:15:53,641
(EXHALES SLOWLY)

293
00:15:56,481 --> 00:15:57,841
(METAL CLANKS)

294
00:16:05,561 --> 00:16:08,321
(ON COMMS) Leader,
we are on optimal proximity

295
00:16:08,441 --> 00:16:09,801
to Boundary.

296
00:16:09,921 --> 00:16:13,841
Boundary gateway is reopening.

297
00:16:21,561 --> 00:16:23,841
GRAHAM;
We've got to get off this ship.

298
00:16:36,281 --> 00:16:39,161
(BREATHES SLOWLY)

299
00:16:40,361 --> 00:16:42,681
MASTER: Welcome, Doctor.

300
00:16:44,321 --> 00:16:45,601
Are you suffering comfortably?

301
00:16:47,081 --> 00:16:48,161
Then, I'll begin.

302
00:16:50,641 --> 00:16:51,681
Once upon a time...

303
00:16:51,801 --> 00:16:52,841
No.

304
00:16:54,721 --> 00:16:57,641
Once upon several times,

305
00:16:57,761 --> 00:16:59,521
before the Time Lords,

306
00:16:59,641 --> 00:17:01,881
before everything we know,

307
00:17:02,001 --> 00:17:03,601
there was an explorer.

308
00:17:03,721 --> 00:17:06,401
Her name was Tecteun...

309
00:17:07,641 --> 00:17:11,081
...from a little-regarded,
sparsely populated planet

310
00:17:11,201 --> 00:17:13,321
called Gallifrey.

311
00:17:13,441 --> 00:17:16,641
Tecteun was the first
of Gallifrey's indigenous race,

312
00:17:16,761 --> 00:17:19,121
the Shobogans,
to develop space travel.

313
00:17:20,321 --> 00:17:23,201
Dangerous,
unsophisticated space travel.

314
00:17:24,401 --> 00:17:28,441
She took risks to explore
the worlds and galaxies

315
00:17:28,561 --> 00:17:30,041
beyond her home.

316
00:17:30,161 --> 00:17:33,081
And it was on one of these
distant deserted worlds

317
00:17:33,201 --> 00:17:34,681
on the far edge
of another galaxy

318
00:17:34,801 --> 00:17:36,161
she found something...

319
00:17:37,241 --> 00:17:38,641
...impossible.

320
00:17:39,841 --> 00:17:40,961
A gateway.

321
00:17:42,161 --> 00:17:45,961
A boundary into another
unknown dimension or universe.

322
00:17:47,521 --> 00:17:50,081
Tecteun glimpsed the infinite

323
00:17:50,201 --> 00:17:52,001
through that gateway.

324
00:17:53,241 --> 00:17:55,161
And beneath the monument
she found...

325
00:17:56,241 --> 00:17:57,241
...a child.

326
00:17:58,521 --> 00:17:59,921
Abandoned.

327
00:18:00,041 --> 00:18:01,441
Alone.

328
00:18:01,561 --> 00:18:05,081
Thrown through, seemingly,
from the other unknown realm.

329
00:18:06,401 --> 00:18:09,321
Tecteun had a choice to make -

330
00:18:09,441 --> 00:18:12,241
abandon or save the child?

331
00:18:12,361 --> 00:18:14,561
She chose
to rescue the foundling

332
00:18:14,681 --> 00:18:18,321
and adopt this refugee
from another realm as her own.

333
00:18:19,361 --> 00:18:21,881
Together,
they explored the universe.

334
00:18:22,001 --> 00:18:23,881
The child grew older,

335
00:18:24,001 --> 00:18:27,081
and finally Tecteun
returned to Gallifrey

336
00:18:27,201 --> 00:18:28,801
with her new child.

337
00:18:28,921 --> 00:18:31,041
Like any parent,

338
00:18:31,161 --> 00:18:34,201
Tecteun wanted
to understand her child.

339
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:38,161
She searched for clues
as to the child's identity -

340
00:18:38,281 --> 00:18:42,441
where she might be from,
what species she could be.

341
00:18:42,561 --> 00:18:44,161
But the child would not yield

342
00:18:44,281 --> 00:18:46,601
any secrets
Tecteun could understand.

343
00:18:46,721 --> 00:18:50,241
The child remained a mystery...

344
00:18:51,321 --> 00:18:52,961
.until...

345
00:18:53,081 --> 00:18:56,921
Playing with a friend,
like any other child...

346
00:18:58,241 --> 00:19:00,081
...there was an accident.

347
00:19:01,481 --> 00:19:03,121
A catastrophe...

348
00:19:06,761 --> 00:19:09,281
...Tor Tecteun,

349
00:19:09,401 --> 00:19:12,281
for the child she'd saved,

350
00:19:12,401 --> 00:19:13,681
now lost to her.

351
00:19:17,041 --> 00:19:18,441
Or so she thought.

352
00:19:38,041 --> 00:19:39,761
The child regenerated.

353
00:19:41,401 --> 00:19:44,121
The first regeneration
of any person

354
00:19:44,241 --> 00:19:46,401
on the planet of Gallifrey.

355
00:19:49,681 --> 00:19:51,721
(LOW RUMBLING)

356
00:19:55,201 --> 00:19:57,481
(RUMBLING GROWS LOUDER)

357
00:20:14,081 --> 00:20:16,801
Boundary force field gateway
now closed.

358
00:20:16,921 --> 00:20:21,281
There is no escape for humans.

359
00:20:34,921 --> 00:20:37,121
First trap's sprung. They fell
for the old bio-dampener

360
00:20:37,241 --> 00:20:39,721
Decoy Human Signal trick -
textbook! (LAUGHS)

361
00:20:45,201 --> 00:20:47,361
Thought they'd last longer
than that.

362
00:20:55,121 --> 00:20:57,841
KO SHARMUS: All right, Ryan,
they're on the march.

363
00:20:57,961 --> 00:21:00,281
You know what to do.
We're relying on you.

364
00:21:00,401 --> 00:21:02,321
Did I mention I've never been
the greatest shot?

365
00:21:03,641 --> 00:21:04,761
Now!

366
00:21:04,881 --> 00:21:07,401
(TICKING)

367
00:21:15,761 --> 00:21:17,281
Whoa! I did it!

368
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:20,481
In the hoop! Swish! (LAUGHS)

369
00:21:20,601 --> 00:21:21,881
Great shot!

370
00:21:22,001 --> 00:21:24,601
You come for humans,
you come for me,

371
00:21:24,721 --> 00:21:26,041
Ryan Sinclair!

372
00:21:26,161 --> 00:21:28,521
We defeated the Cybermen.

373
00:21:28,641 --> 00:21:30,641
Well, me. Technically, it's me.
Oh!

374
00:21:30,761 --> 00:21:33,201
There are always more.
Get inside now.

375
00:21:33,321 --> 00:21:35,161
Now!

376
00:21:42,721 --> 00:21:45,241
MASTER: Ah! Ah!

377
00:21:45,361 --> 00:21:47,241
Come in.

378
00:21:47,361 --> 00:21:48,681
Come in!

379
00:21:50,041 --> 00:21:51,921
No, don't...don't worry
about her.

380
00:21:52,041 --> 00:21:54,841
She's fully under my control.

381
00:21:56,121 --> 00:21:58,481
Congratulations.

382
00:21:58,601 --> 00:21:59,881
You have managed something

383
00:22:00,001 --> 00:22:02,201
no other Cyberman
ever achieved,

384
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:05,521
maybe - maybe -
even dreamed of!

385
00:22:05,641 --> 00:22:08,561
Gallifrey is yours.

386
00:22:09,921 --> 00:22:12,401
Offered as a gift.

387
00:22:14,081 --> 00:22:16,441
From an admiring Master.

388
00:22:18,041 --> 00:22:20,721
I know our races
have been enemies.

389
00:22:20,841 --> 00:22:22,881
I lived through
the Great Cyber War.

390
00:22:23,001 --> 00:22:25,921
I saw the atrocities
perpetrated on your race.

391
00:22:26,041 --> 00:22:28,161
I want to help put that right.
(SNIFFS)

392
00:22:28,281 --> 00:22:29,921
Why?

393
00:22:30,041 --> 00:22:32,401
I fear we have
a common interest.

394
00:22:34,161 --> 00:22:38,881
The new Cyber-army
shall have one goal -

395
00:22:39,001 --> 00:22:42,401
the destruction
of all organic life.

396
00:22:42,521 --> 00:22:44,961
Ah! So that's your thinking.

397
00:22:47,041 --> 00:22:48,681
But how are you going
to manage that?

398
00:22:48,801 --> 00:22:51,321
The Death Particle.

399
00:22:52,641 --> 00:22:55,081
One Particle, when activated,

400
00:22:55,201 --> 00:22:59,481
capable of destroying
all organic life.

401
00:22:59,601 --> 00:23:01,201
Very nice!

402
00:23:01,321 --> 00:23:02,561
Ooh!

403
00:23:02,681 --> 00:23:04,721
(PULSATES)

404
00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:06,241
Did you make that?

405
00:23:06,361 --> 00:23:08,881
The Cyberium created it...

406
00:23:10,881 --> 00:23:13,001
...through me.

407
00:23:13,121 --> 00:23:15,881
So you're the host...

408
00:23:16,001 --> 00:23:20,001
...for all Cyber knowledge
and strategy.

409
00:23:21,081 --> 00:23:22,841
Oh. Interesting.

410
00:23:22,961 --> 00:23:26,281
Now, I hate to point out
the flaw in your plan -

411
00:23:26,401 --> 00:23:29,281
Cybermen are part organic,

412
00:23:29,401 --> 00:23:31,561
but you more than most.

413
00:23:31,681 --> 00:23:33,681
My new Cyberwarriors

414
00:23:33,801 --> 00:23:37,801
are purged
of organic components.

415
00:23:37,921 --> 00:23:40,961
We shall rise towards
full automation,

416
00:23:41,081 --> 00:23:44,481
driven by the intelligence
of the Cyberium.

417
00:23:47,801 --> 00:23:50,121
And when that work is done...

418
00:23:51,361 --> 00:23:57,521
...I shall join my warriors
and make the final ascension

419
00:23:57,641 --> 00:24:00,561
to full mechanisation!

420
00:24:00,681 --> 00:24:02,641
Oh, you mean robots.

421
00:24:04,121 --> 00:24:05,681
You'll be robots.

422
00:24:07,841 --> 00:24:11,361
We shall be dominant.

423
00:24:11,481 --> 00:24:13,001
But robots.

424
00:24:13,121 --> 00:24:16,321
Oof. I'm a bit disappointed.

425
00:24:16,441 --> 00:24:17,521
I see how you got there -

426
00:24:17,641 --> 00:24:19,801
an Al wanting to create
more things in its own image -

427
00:24:19,921 --> 00:24:21,041
but it lacks vision.

428
00:24:21,161 --> 00:24:23,641
Right, what if we, um,
workshop this?

429
00:24:23,761 --> 00:24:25,361
You know, kick it around a bit?

430
00:24:25,481 --> 00:24:26,921
I have notes.

431
00:24:27,041 --> 00:24:30,561
You question the strategy
of the Cyberium?

432
00:24:30,681 --> 00:24:34,121
I do. I mean, it's good,
but it's not great.

433
00:24:34,241 --> 00:24:36,321
There's loads of robots.

434
00:24:36,441 --> 00:24:38,361
Throw a stick in this universe,
you'll hit a robot.

435
00:24:38,481 --> 00:24:39,961
I used to do that.

436
00:24:40,081 --> 00:24:42,681
Any idiot can make themselves
into a robot.

437
00:24:42,801 --> 00:24:44,201
It's not special.

438
00:24:45,601 --> 00:24:46,601
(WHIRRING)

439
00:24:46,721 --> 00:24:47,641
But if you want to be

440
00:24:47,761 --> 00:24:49,841
the dominant force
in the universe...

441
00:24:52,441 --> 00:24:53,841
...I can facilitate that.

442
00:24:58,161 --> 00:24:59,921
(GROANS)

443
00:25:00,041 --> 00:25:01,921
Explain.

444
00:25:02,041 --> 00:25:05,201
How fast are the conversion
processes on your ship?

445
00:25:05,321 --> 00:25:08,441
They have been restored
to optimal efficiency.

446
00:25:08,561 --> 00:25:12,001
(GROANS) Good. Good, good.
Good.

447
00:25:12,121 --> 00:25:14,441
Good!

448
00:25:14,561 --> 00:25:16,921
Cos I burned the Citadel,

449
00:25:17,041 --> 00:25:19,801
but if I have one weakness,
it's that I am...

450
00:25:19,921 --> 00:25:21,481
...a bit of a hoarder.

451
00:25:21,601 --> 00:25:23,041
Let me show you.

452
00:25:23,161 --> 00:25:24,241
(GRUNTS)

453
00:25:25,321 --> 00:25:28,761
She's waking up in that Matrix.
But don't worry,

454
00:25:28,881 --> 00:25:31,161
my consciousness
can deal with her.

455
00:25:31,281 --> 00:25:34,521
I'm that good -
I can be in two places at once.

456
00:25:34,641 --> 00:25:36,121
(LAUGHS MANIACALLY)

457
00:25:40,281 --> 00:25:42,481
Now, having seen
her adopted child

458
00:25:42,601 --> 00:25:44,121
regenerate her body,

459
00:25:44,241 --> 00:25:47,321
Tecteun,
a scientist and explorer,

460
00:25:47,441 --> 00:25:50,161
had a new landscape to explore.

461
00:25:52,481 --> 00:25:55,601
She dedicated her life
to studying her child.

462
00:25:56,921 --> 00:26:00,041
Detailed every fragment
of genetic material.

463
00:26:00,161 --> 00:26:01,401
It took her years...

464
00:26:02,921 --> 00:26:05,321
...several of the child's
regenerations.

465
00:26:19,921 --> 00:26:21,561
Tecteun grew older.

466
00:26:21,681 --> 00:26:25,361
Her desire to understand
became an obsession.

467
00:26:25,481 --> 00:26:29,841
She worked tirelessly,
endlessly, furiously.

468
00:26:29,961 --> 00:26:34,521
She had to crack this code
to understand regeneration.

469
00:26:35,961 --> 00:26:37,081
And finally...

470
00:26:38,601 --> 00:26:39,881
...she did.

471
00:26:41,521 --> 00:26:45,841
And to prove herself right,
she took the ultimate risk.

472
00:26:49,001 --> 00:26:52,321
Tested the theory on herself.

473
00:26:52,441 --> 00:26:54,481
Put her own life on the line.

474
00:26:54,601 --> 00:26:56,521
(GRUNTS)

475
00:26:56,641 --> 00:26:59,201
(BUZZING)

476
00:27:02,041 --> 00:27:03,601
Spliced into herself

477
00:27:03,721 --> 00:27:06,401
the genetic ability
to regenerate.

478
00:27:09,681 --> 00:27:11,481
I didn't know any of this.

479
00:27:14,521 --> 00:27:15,761
Did you know any of this?

480
00:27:18,481 --> 00:27:20,321
(SIGHS) Nearly there.

481
00:27:21,801 --> 00:27:24,561
The planet of Gallifrey
evolved.

482
00:27:24,681 --> 00:27:27,841
Shobogans grew
in knowledge and ability.

483
00:27:27,961 --> 00:27:31,081
They built themselves
the Citadel.

484
00:27:31,201 --> 00:27:33,201
They discovered the ability
to travel through time

485
00:27:33,321 --> 00:27:34,761
as well as space.

486
00:27:36,041 --> 00:27:41,081
With Tecteun, they became
a self-appointed ruling elite.

487
00:27:41,201 --> 00:27:43,921
And Tecteun proposed

488
00:27:44,041 --> 00:27:47,081
that he gene-splice
the ability to regenerate

489
00:27:47,201 --> 00:27:50,841
into future generations
of Citadel-dwellers.

490
00:27:50,961 --> 00:27:53,561
It would become
the genetic inheritance of them

491
00:27:53,681 --> 00:27:55,761
and their descendants.

492
00:27:55,881 --> 00:27:58,561
But he would restrict
the regenerative process

493
00:27:58,681 --> 00:28:00,761
to a maximum of 12 times.

494
00:28:00,881 --> 00:28:04,161
The timeless child became
the base genetic code

495
00:28:04,281 --> 00:28:07,201
for all Gallifreyans
within the citadel.

496
00:28:07,321 --> 00:28:09,841
The civilisation
which renamed themselves -

497
00:28:09,961 --> 00:28:12,921
with characteristic pomposity -

498
00:28:13,041 --> 00:28:15,201
Time Lords.

499
00:28:16,961 --> 00:28:20,641
The foundling
had become the founder.

500
00:28:26,601 --> 00:28:30,041
The rest, as they say,
is history.

501
00:28:31,521 --> 00:28:34,001
What happened to the child?

502
00:28:37,281 --> 00:28:39,361
(CHUCKLES)

503
00:28:39,481 --> 00:28:40,841
What?

504
00:28:42,081 --> 00:28:43,561
What's so funny?

505
00:28:44,881 --> 00:28:47,721
What happened to the child?!

506
00:28:48,801 --> 00:28:50,321
Oh, Doctor, really?

507
00:28:52,001 --> 00:28:53,761
Haven't you
worked this out yet?

508
00:29:00,521 --> 00:29:01,641
The child is you.

509
00:29:04,761 --> 00:29:06,561
(INHALES SHARPLY)

510
00:29:09,001 --> 00:29:11,601
You are the timeless child.

511
00:29:12,961 --> 00:29:14,121
(BREATH QUICKENS)

512
00:29:14,241 --> 00:29:15,721
No.

513
00:29:15,841 --> 00:29:17,241
No, I'm not.

514
00:29:18,521 --> 00:29:20,001
You always have been.

515
00:29:20,121 --> 00:29:22,561
I can't be.

516
00:29:24,041 --> 00:29:26,201
(BREATH QUICKENS)

517
00:29:29,481 --> 00:29:30,561
(SCREAMS)

518
00:29:30,681 --> 00:29:32,721
KO SHARMUS: Come on, come on!
Hurry, hurry!

519
00:29:34,721 --> 00:29:37,601
- This place is like a maze.
- I made it that way.

520
00:29:37,721 --> 00:29:39,961
In case of an eventuality
like this.

521
00:29:40,081 --> 00:29:41,841
Hey, you never think of doors?

522
00:29:41,961 --> 00:29:43,241
Big, lockable doors.

523
00:29:43,361 --> 00:29:44,761
Indestructible doors.

524
00:29:44,881 --> 00:29:46,001
Dream of them every night!

525
00:29:46,121 --> 00:29:47,441
But I had to work
with what I had.

526
00:29:47,561 --> 00:29:49,241
Now...

527
00:29:49,361 --> 00:29:52,041
Hide well,
take what shots you can.

528
00:29:52,161 --> 00:29:54,361
Kill them before they kill you.

529
00:29:54,481 --> 00:29:56,601
Go!

530
00:30:01,561 --> 00:30:04,441
Three human life forms
detected.

531
00:30:15,801 --> 00:30:18,401
(RATTLING)

532
00:30:28,481 --> 00:30:30,481
- (KNOCKING)
- Hello.

533
00:30:31,681 --> 00:30:33,081
Too many of them.

534
00:30:38,361 --> 00:30:42,041
- One human located.
- No! No...

535
00:30:42,161 --> 00:30:44,401
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS)

536
00:30:44,521 --> 00:30:47,601
All humans will be executed.

537
00:30:51,721 --> 00:30:52,761
(COCKS BLASTER)

538
00:30:52,881 --> 00:30:54,321
(BLASTER POWERS UP)

539
00:30:55,921 --> 00:30:58,521
- Oh! Oh, my days...
- Oh, my saints...

540
00:30:59,641 --> 00:31:01,601
BOTH: Where's Ethan?

541
00:31:01,721 --> 00:31:04,041
CYBERWARRIOR: Attention,
remaining humans.

542
00:31:04,161 --> 00:31:05,161
We have your friend.

543
00:31:05,281 --> 00:31:07,881
You have ten seconds
to surrender

544
00:31:08,001 --> 00:31:09,961
or he will be executed.

545
00:31:10,081 --> 00:31:12,321
- Don't come for me. Argh!
- Ten...

546
00:31:12,441 --> 00:31:15,041
He's two pathways away.
This way.

547
00:31:15,161 --> 00:31:16,161
Hey! We're coming!
We surrender!

548
00:31:16,281 --> 00:31:18,001
- Stop!
- Five, four...

549
00:31:18,121 --> 00:31:19,881
- I said, "We surrender!"
- ...three...

550
00:31:20,001 --> 00:31:21,761
- We surrender!
- ...two, one...

551
00:31:21,881 --> 00:31:23,041
- No!
- (BLASTS)

552
00:31:23,161 --> 00:31:25,401
(METAL RATTLES)

553
00:31:33,601 --> 00:31:34,801
I don't understand.

554
00:31:41,041 --> 00:31:42,881
How about now?

555
00:31:47,321 --> 00:31:48,281
GRAHAM: Uh, Yaz,

556
00:31:48,401 --> 00:31:49,961
I can't...can't
get this hat off.

557
00:31:53,201 --> 00:31:54,401
MASTER: Wow...

558
00:31:54,521 --> 00:31:56,241
Wow.

559
00:31:56,361 --> 00:31:58,801
Wow, wow, wow, wow!

560
00:31:58,921 --> 00:32:02,601
Ah!
You have got a lot of these!

561
00:32:04,041 --> 00:32:06,641
A whole Cybercarrier worth.

562
00:32:06,761 --> 00:32:08,881
Perfect.

563
00:32:13,841 --> 00:32:15,241
So, what's your plan now?

564
00:32:15,361 --> 00:32:18,441
The Cyberium will process

565
00:32:18,561 --> 00:32:20,841
and dictate the strategy.

566
00:32:20,961 --> 00:32:22,441
The Cyberium?

567
00:32:23,801 --> 00:32:26,721
I've heard a lot about that
over the millennia.

568
00:32:26,841 --> 00:32:29,521
The heart of all your power.

569
00:32:31,241 --> 00:32:34,521
The centre
of all Cyber knowledge.

570
00:32:35,881 --> 00:32:37,201
(EXHALES)

571
00:32:40,201 --> 00:32:43,841
Oh, come on, Cyberium,
show us some leg.

572
00:32:43,961 --> 00:32:45,641
What do you actually
look like, hmm?

573
00:32:45,761 --> 00:32:48,241
It will not leave me...

574
00:32:48,361 --> 00:32:50,481
...while I live.

575
00:32:50,601 --> 00:32:51,921
Oh.

576
00:32:52,041 --> 00:32:53,641
OK.

577
00:33:09,241 --> 00:33:10,361
(GASPS)

578
00:33:10,481 --> 00:33:12,961
Well, aren't you pretty?

579
00:33:13,081 --> 00:33:15,001
And fast.

580
00:33:15,121 --> 00:33:17,401
You made your exit
very swiftly there.

581
00:33:17,521 --> 00:33:18,601
Worried, were you?

582
00:33:31,281 --> 00:33:32,841
I thought if he was compressed,

583
00:33:32,961 --> 00:33:35,361
the Death Particle
would activate...

584
00:33:36,561 --> 00:33:37,921
(SIGHS)

585
00:33:38,041 --> 00:33:39,441
...and all this would be over.

586
00:33:41,321 --> 00:33:42,721
I would've been OK with that.

587
00:33:45,281 --> 00:33:48,161
I thought it was a nice little
gamble, but no. (GROANS)

588
00:33:48,281 --> 00:33:49,481
Here we are.

589
00:33:50,601 --> 00:33:52,401
All still alive.

590
00:33:54,801 --> 00:34:00,561
And one miniaturised
Death Particle still in him,

591
00:34:00,681 --> 00:34:02,241
waiting for its moment...

592
00:34:03,601 --> 00:34:07,241
...for its chamber
to be smashed open.

593
00:34:07,361 --> 00:34:11,121
Prrrksh!

594
00:34:11,241 --> 00:34:12,841
Oh! (SNAPS)

595
00:34:12,961 --> 00:34:14,161
Shoot!

596
00:34:14,281 --> 00:34:17,281
I should've said, "Somebody
needs to cut you down to size",

597
00:34:17,401 --> 00:34:18,721
then zapped you.

598
00:34:18,841 --> 00:34:21,041
(GIGGLES)
I was just trigger-happy.

599
00:34:21,161 --> 00:34:23,841
(SIGHS) I'll use it next time.

600
00:34:23,961 --> 00:34:26,041
Sit there for a mo.

601
00:34:26,161 --> 00:34:28,121
Oh, sorry, were you close?

602
00:34:29,681 --> 00:34:31,081
Candidly,

603
00:34:31,201 --> 00:34:32,961
I think you can do better.

604
00:34:34,001 --> 00:34:36,001
I request an alliance.

605
00:34:36,121 --> 00:34:37,761
I deserve to be
your business partner

606
00:34:37,881 --> 00:34:40,361
because I have performed well
in all the tasks.

607
00:34:40,481 --> 00:34:45,121
I ransacked the Matrix
of the Time Lords,

608
00:34:45,241 --> 00:34:48,761
distilled all the knowledge,
all the experiences,

609
00:34:48,881 --> 00:34:50,521
all the discoveries,

610
00:34:50,641 --> 00:34:52,681
into these brains up here.

611
00:34:52,801 --> 00:34:57,081
All the Cyber knowledge,
all the Time Lord knowledge...

612
00:34:57,201 --> 00:34:59,641
(LAUGHS) Put it together,
what do you get?

613
00:35:01,361 --> 00:35:03,761
Absolute supremacy
in the universe.

614
00:35:05,401 --> 00:35:06,401
Choose me.

615
00:35:06,521 --> 00:35:08,361
Oh, wow!

616
00:35:08,481 --> 00:35:10,601
That was quick! (CACKLES)

617
00:35:10,721 --> 00:35:12,241
Wa-ha-ha! Whoa!

618
00:35:12,361 --> 00:35:14,041
Woohoo!

619
00:35:14,161 --> 00:35:17,881
At least buy me...dinner!
(SHRIEKS)

620
00:35:19,881 --> 00:35:21,401
(ECHOING LAUGHTER)

621
00:35:23,201 --> 00:35:25,161
MASTER: This is no time
to be sleeping.

622
00:35:27,561 --> 00:35:29,681
Is it hurting, Doctor?

623
00:35:30,721 --> 00:35:34,241
I hope it's hurting,
because it really hurt me.

624
00:35:36,041 --> 00:35:37,161
It's all lies.

625
00:35:39,321 --> 00:35:40,921
None of this is the truth.

626
00:35:41,041 --> 00:35:42,721
For the first time in my lives,

627
00:35:42,841 --> 00:35:46,401
I can honestly say
every word is true.

628
00:35:46,521 --> 00:35:47,521
I know my life.

629
00:35:50,441 --> 00:35:51,801
I know...

630
00:35:51,921 --> 00:35:53,561
I know who I am.

631
00:35:53,681 --> 00:35:55,921
No, you don't. You never have.

632
00:35:56,041 --> 00:35:59,241
Your life has been hidden
from you.

633
00:35:59,361 --> 00:36:02,041
Our founding parents
wanted a noble creation myth

634
00:36:02,161 --> 00:36:03,361
for the Time Lords.

635
00:36:04,521 --> 00:36:05,601
"Born To Rule".

636
00:36:05,721 --> 00:36:06,881
I remember my home.

637
00:36:08,601 --> 00:36:09,841
I remember growing up.

638
00:36:09,961 --> 00:36:12,561
I remember you and me
at the Academy together.

639
00:36:12,681 --> 00:36:14,201
That happened.

640
00:36:14,321 --> 00:36:15,801
It just wasn't your first life.

641
00:36:15,921 --> 00:36:17,681
Why would they lie?!

642
00:36:19,561 --> 00:36:20,921
Why would they do that?

643
00:36:22,201 --> 00:36:25,041
I wish it wasn't true,
but it is.

644
00:36:27,481 --> 00:36:29,481
You know what I find
the most infuriating?

645
00:36:30,601 --> 00:36:32,561
You always behaved
like you were different,

646
00:36:32,681 --> 00:36:34,561
like you were... like
you were special.

647
00:36:35,801 --> 00:36:37,481
And you were.

648
00:36:40,241 --> 00:36:41,481
You can see...

649
00:36:41,601 --> 00:36:43,481
You can see why I'm angry.

650
00:36:43,601 --> 00:36:46,001
(STAMMERS)
A little piece of you is in me.

651
00:36:47,201 --> 00:36:48,961
AILT am is somehow
because of you,

652
00:36:49,081 --> 00:36:52,041
and believe me when I say,
I cannot bear that!

653
00:36:54,881 --> 00:36:56,321
Show me the rest.

654
00:36:57,361 --> 00:36:58,841
I'm not sure you can cope
with much...

655
00:36:58,961 --> 00:37:01,201
Show me the rest!

656
00:37:02,441 --> 00:37:05,081
I have a right
to know my own life.

657
00:37:05,201 --> 00:37:06,881
(LAUGHS)

658
00:37:10,281 --> 00:37:12,041
All right.

659
00:37:12,161 --> 00:37:14,881
But I'm not sure
it's going to make you happy.

660
00:37:16,601 --> 00:37:19,441
The policy of the Time Lords
is clear -

661
00:37:19,561 --> 00:37:23,401
strict non-intervention
in other worlds and times.

662
00:37:28,521 --> 00:37:29,961
However...

663
00:37:31,321 --> 00:37:35,361
Policy and reality
sometimes diverge.

664
00:37:36,841 --> 00:37:39,561
There are times when
it is necessary to intervene.

665
00:37:40,961 --> 00:37:43,441
That is the purpose
of The Division.

666
00:37:45,241 --> 00:37:47,001
The tests we set you...

667
00:37:49,401 --> 00:37:51,601
These results are the best
I've ever seen.

668
00:37:51,721 --> 00:37:56,121
Those images.
Island. I've seen them...

669
00:37:56,241 --> 00:37:57,721
...in my head.

670
00:37:57,841 --> 00:37:59,681
What are they?

671
00:37:59,801 --> 00:38:01,481
Sh-sh-sh-sh.

672
00:38:01,601 --> 00:38:03,241
She's talking.

673
00:38:03,361 --> 00:38:06,441
The Division does not exist.

674
00:38:07,521 --> 00:38:10,561
The Division does not
have operatives.

675
00:38:10,681 --> 00:38:13,721
We are not even here.

676
00:38:15,401 --> 00:38:17,041
Do you understand?

677
00:38:18,841 --> 00:38:20,961
I propose...

678
00:38:23,561 --> 00:38:24,721
What have you done?

679
00:38:24,841 --> 00:38:26,241
Not me.

680
00:38:26,361 --> 00:38:28,241
That was done
long before I got here.

681
00:38:29,881 --> 00:38:34,001
Everything from here
is redacted, blocked out,

682
00:38:34,121 --> 00:38:35,761
all but erased.

683
00:38:37,361 --> 00:38:39,361
There was something here.

684
00:38:39,481 --> 00:38:40,721
A lot of stuff, seemingly,

685
00:38:40,841 --> 00:38:42,721
but now it all
just looks like this.

686
00:38:42,841 --> 00:38:46,161
I tried everything,
everything, to decode it,

687
00:38:46,281 --> 00:38:50,281
but it's...it's unrecoverable,
beyond even my brilliance.

688
00:38:50,401 --> 00:38:52,721
And it's not often I say that.
(CHUCKLES)

689
00:38:54,121 --> 00:38:55,561
But it's my life.

690
00:38:58,521 --> 00:39:00,401
Yeah.

691
00:39:00,521 --> 00:39:03,121
How much was lost?

692
00:39:03,241 --> 00:39:05,641
Impossible to tell.

693
00:39:05,761 --> 00:39:08,241
It took up a lot of space
in the Matrix, though.

694
00:39:08,361 --> 00:39:10,441
Yeah.

695
00:39:10,561 --> 00:39:12,001
There is one final trace.

696
00:39:12,121 --> 00:39:16,401
Those glitches of Island
you keep seeing.

697
00:39:16,521 --> 00:39:20,241
Those images, they were buried
deep in the Matrix.

698
00:39:20,361 --> 00:39:22,121
Tecteun put
a visual filter over it

699
00:39:22,241 --> 00:39:25,921
so that no-one who watched it
would find it remarkable.

700
00:39:26,041 --> 00:39:27,121
(YELPS)

701
00:39:27,241 --> 00:39:28,561
I transmitted them
into your mind

702
00:39:28,681 --> 00:39:30,361
as you tracked the Cybermen.

703
00:39:31,401 --> 00:39:34,481
Maybe this is
the last gift of a parent.

704
00:39:34,601 --> 00:39:36,281
A clue.

705
00:39:37,321 --> 00:39:38,641
Or an apology.

706
00:39:41,241 --> 00:39:42,361
You can decide.

707
00:39:42,481 --> 00:39:47,081
Did Tecteun leave these images
for you to decode one day?

708
00:39:50,001 --> 00:39:52,721
We have to get rid
of everything, I'm afraid.

709
00:39:52,841 --> 00:39:54,761
Thank you for your service.

710
00:39:56,481 --> 00:39:58,921
We're sorry
you won't remember it.

711
00:40:01,601 --> 00:40:02,681
(SHRIEKING)

712
00:40:02,801 --> 00:40:04,081
(CLOCK TICKS)

713
00:40:19,361 --> 00:40:21,361
What did they do to you,
Doctor?

714
00:40:21,481 --> 00:40:23,241
How many lives have you had?

715
00:40:23,361 --> 00:40:24,281
Wake up.

716
00:40:24,601 --> 00:40:26,161
(GASPS)

717
00:40:36,481 --> 00:40:39,641
I know you're broken,
but it's all over now.

718
00:40:40,841 --> 00:40:42,121
What do you mean?

719
00:40:43,401 --> 00:40:46,481
When I said
I killed everyone here...

720
00:40:48,681 --> 00:40:50,761
...I did keep the bodies.

721
00:40:52,201 --> 00:40:54,841
Just...just cold enough
in case they'd be useful.

722
00:40:54,961 --> 00:40:56,961
I thought...I thought maybe
some good can come

723
00:40:57,081 --> 00:40:59,041
out of all of this.

724
00:41:00,681 --> 00:41:04,121
Your adopted mother isn't the
only one who can experiment.

725
00:41:04,241 --> 00:41:05,761
I mean, what if...

726
00:41:07,161 --> 00:41:10,001
...a new race could be created?

727
00:41:10,121 --> 00:41:12,081
Huh?

728
00:41:13,161 --> 00:41:14,641
(EXHALES EXCITEDLY)

729
00:41:19,161 --> 00:41:22,761
Time Lord organics
with the ability to regenerate

730
00:41:22,881 --> 00:41:26,961
and self-repair
in Cyber arm our!

731
00:41:27,081 --> 00:41:28,001
(GASPS)

732
00:41:28,121 --> 00:41:30,321
Invincible!

733
00:41:30,441 --> 00:41:32,961
The perfect army, right?

734
00:41:33,081 --> 00:41:34,161
Right?!

735
00:41:34,281 --> 00:41:35,841
(LAUGHS EXUBERANTLY)

736
00:41:35,961 --> 00:41:37,681
Oh, come in, my pretties.

737
00:41:37,801 --> 00:41:39,121
Yeah!

738
00:41:39,241 --> 00:41:40,201
(CLANKING)

739
00:41:40,321 --> 00:41:44,001
Doosh, doosh, doosh!

740
00:41:47,801 --> 00:41:51,441
Line up. Attention!
Yeah, that's it.

741
00:41:51,561 --> 00:41:53,081
(LAUGHS)

742
00:41:53,201 --> 00:41:54,361
Grr!

743
00:41:54,481 --> 00:41:56,601
Well, let's test it out.

744
00:42:01,361 --> 00:42:03,001
Shoot him.

745
00:42:03,121 --> 00:42:04,601
Shoot him!

746
00:42:07,521 --> 00:42:08,841
Good dog.

747
00:42:11,681 --> 00:42:12,841
All dead.

748
00:42:12,961 --> 00:42:13,961
Um...

749
00:42:17,001 --> 00:42:18,401
Wait.

750
00:42:18,521 --> 00:42:19,801
Could it be?

751
00:42:21,961 --> 00:42:26,921
Yes, it could!
(LAUGHS MANIACALLY)

752
00:42:33,081 --> 00:42:35,841
(LAUGHS)

753
00:42:37,681 --> 00:42:39,121
(YELLS)

754
00:42:39,241 --> 00:42:43,561
Behold your new CyberMasters,
Doctor.

755
00:42:43,681 --> 00:42:45,881
All born from you!

756
00:42:46,001 --> 00:42:48,801
But led by me.

757
00:42:48,921 --> 00:42:50,321
How does that feel?

758
00:42:52,041 --> 00:42:53,401
Huh?

759
00:42:55,241 --> 00:42:56,881
Now, no time to lose.

760
00:42:57,001 --> 00:42:59,281
Don't move.
Oh, that's right, you can't.

761
00:42:59,401 --> 00:43:00,721
(LAUGHS)

762
00:43:00,841 --> 00:43:05,481
(SIGHS) Can you feel
a new era dawning, Doctor?

763
00:43:09,081 --> 00:43:11,281
- For Gallifrey.
- CYBERGUARDS: For Gallifrey!

764
00:43:11,401 --> 00:43:13,041
For the Time Lords.

765
00:43:13,161 --> 00:43:14,481
CYBERGUARDS:
For the Time Lords!

766
00:43:14,601 --> 00:43:17,761
For the end
of the universe itself!

767
00:43:17,881 --> 00:43:20,321
CYBERGUARDS: For the end
of the universe itself!

768
00:43:20,441 --> 00:43:21,921
Sweet dreams.

769
00:43:24,761 --> 00:43:26,761
This way, soldiers.

770
00:43:33,401 --> 00:43:35,441
RAVIO: The Boundary, it's real!

771
00:43:35,561 --> 00:43:38,081
RYAN: Yeah. And the Doctor's
on the other side.

772
00:43:42,321 --> 00:43:43,481
So, how do we do this?

773
00:43:43,601 --> 00:43:45,521
The Boundary will absorb us.

774
00:43:45,641 --> 00:43:47,441
But you have to take the step.

775
00:43:47,561 --> 00:43:49,441
Step into the unknown.

776
00:43:49,561 --> 00:43:51,561
Who fancies going first?

777
00:43:53,401 --> 00:43:54,721
Ah!

778
00:44:03,481 --> 00:44:04,841
This is Gallifrey.

779
00:44:06,561 --> 00:44:08,401
This is where
the Doctor's from.

780
00:44:10,761 --> 00:44:12,761
We're never going to find her
in this lot.

781
00:44:12,881 --> 00:44:13,801
Yeah, we are.

782
00:44:13,921 --> 00:44:15,721
We're going to find her
and we're going to rescue her.

783
00:44:15,841 --> 00:44:18,801
She's done it for us enough
times. Now it's our turn.

784
00:44:20,241 --> 00:44:22,401
This is going to be even more
dangerous from here.

785
00:44:22,521 --> 00:44:23,481
You don't have to come.

786
00:44:23,601 --> 00:44:25,081
We owe you.

787
00:44:26,321 --> 00:44:28,561
We're in. Right?

788
00:44:28,681 --> 00:44:29,921
Right.

789
00:44:30,041 --> 00:44:32,081
Great. How am I meant
to contradict that,

790
00:44:32,201 --> 00:44:33,401
if you're going all heroic?

791
00:44:36,121 --> 00:44:37,561
You coming?

792
00:44:38,721 --> 00:44:41,201
I already lived
longer than I expected.

793
00:44:41,321 --> 00:44:43,961
There must be a few last things
I can blow up before I'm done.

794
00:45:00,041 --> 00:45:02,041
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

795
00:45:02,161 --> 00:45:03,601
Oh, great.

796
00:45:03,721 --> 00:45:04,841
(SIGHS)

797
00:45:06,801 --> 00:45:08,881
What are you doing here?

798
00:45:11,681 --> 00:45:14,401
Or are you the Matrix
playing more games with me?

799
00:45:14,521 --> 00:45:18,721
Don't ask me.
I'm as lost as you are in here.

800
00:45:18,841 --> 00:45:22,801
Maybe...you just summoned me.

801
00:45:22,921 --> 00:45:25,081
Where do you fit into all this?

802
00:45:26,881 --> 00:45:28,641
Were you me all that time ago?

803
00:45:30,241 --> 00:45:32,681
Were all my memories
of you erased?

804
00:45:34,641 --> 00:45:38,161
Did they force me back
into becoming a child?

805
00:45:42,321 --> 00:45:44,201
How many more of me
are out there?

806
00:45:44,321 --> 00:45:45,921
I don't have those answers.

807
00:45:47,041 --> 00:45:49,281
But say I did -

808
00:45:49,401 --> 00:45:51,081
would they even help?

809
00:45:54,161 --> 00:45:56,361
Of course they would.

810
00:45:56,481 --> 00:45:57,961
All this?

811
00:45:58,081 --> 00:45:59,641
It means I'm not
who I thought I was.

812
00:45:59,761 --> 00:46:01,801
Because your memories
aren't compatible

813
00:46:01,921 --> 00:46:03,481
with what you've learnt today?

814
00:46:03,601 --> 00:46:05,321
Yes.

815
00:46:05,441 --> 00:46:10,201
Have you ever been limited
by who you were before?

816
00:46:13,361 --> 00:46:14,681
Ah.

817
00:46:15,881 --> 00:46:18,121
Now, that does sound
like me talking.

818
00:46:23,601 --> 00:46:25,081
I'm so tired!

819
00:46:26,521 --> 00:46:30,201
The Matrix is sapping
all the energy out of me.

820
00:46:30,321 --> 00:46:32,241
No time to be tired.

821
00:46:32,361 --> 00:46:34,041
Still work to do out there.

822
00:46:34,161 --> 00:46:35,721
Lives at stake.

823
00:46:35,841 --> 00:46:37,081
Armies being born.

824
00:46:38,281 --> 00:46:40,401
People need the Doctor.

825
00:46:48,121 --> 00:46:50,001
I don't know
how to stop the Master.

826
00:46:50,121 --> 00:46:51,841
Course you do.

827
00:46:55,161 --> 00:46:56,681
That one question

828
00:46:56,801 --> 00:46:58,801
that's nagging at you,

829
00:46:58,921 --> 00:47:02,681
the one thing he said
that you didn't understand.

830
00:47:02,801 --> 00:47:04,401
The one thing who said?

831
00:47:04,521 --> 00:47:07,081
- The Master?
- No!

832
00:47:08,721 --> 00:47:10,401
Get out of here.

833
00:47:10,521 --> 00:47:12,761
I know this place
has blown your mind.

834
00:47:14,921 --> 00:47:17,201
Maybe you should return
the compliment.

835
00:47:21,281 --> 00:47:22,281
No, wait!

836
00:47:23,761 --> 00:47:25,321
Are you still there?

837
00:47:25,441 --> 00:47:27,201
Of course she's still there.

838
00:47:27,321 --> 00:47:29,721
If you were me,
you're buried within me,

839
00:47:29,841 --> 00:47:31,561
buried within him...

840
00:47:33,401 --> 00:47:34,721
Too many thoughts.

841
00:47:34,841 --> 00:47:37,081
All right, first things first,
what did she say?

842
00:47:38,361 --> 00:47:40,201
Mind blown.

843
00:47:40,321 --> 00:47:42,081
Yes! Of course.

844
00:47:44,201 --> 00:47:48,921
All this history,
all these lies,

845
00:47:49,041 --> 00:47:51,241
it's too much stimulus.

846
00:47:51,361 --> 00:47:53,081
It might work.

847
00:47:53,201 --> 00:47:56,001
I've fought the Matrix before,
denied its reality,

848
00:47:56,121 --> 00:47:58,201
I can do it again.

849
00:47:58,321 --> 00:47:59,241
Maybe.

850
00:47:59,361 --> 00:48:00,921
Well, you know
what they say, Doctor -

851
00:48:01,041 --> 00:48:02,481
nothing ventured,
nothing blown.

852
00:48:02,601 --> 00:48:03,601
Oh!

853
00:48:03,721 --> 00:48:05,321
I'm talking to myself again.
That's a good sign.

854
00:48:05,441 --> 00:48:06,721
Thanks, Doctor. Still here.

855
00:48:06,841 --> 00:48:08,321
No, shut up,
I need to concentrate.

856
00:48:08,441 --> 00:48:09,521
Uh...

857
00:48:12,401 --> 00:48:13,761
All right.

858
00:48:13,881 --> 00:48:15,521
Have a blast of this, Matrix.

859
00:48:53,361 --> 00:48:54,641
YAZ: Doctor!

860
00:48:56,521 --> 00:49:00,761
GRAHAM: Yaz, is she all right?
Doctor?

861
00:49:03,561 --> 00:49:05,161
Doctor, we're here for you.

862
00:49:14,801 --> 00:49:16,321
My fam.

863
00:49:16,441 --> 00:49:17,841
She's not dead, then.

864
00:49:19,841 --> 00:49:23,201
Who are they?
Are we having a party?

865
00:49:23,321 --> 00:49:24,321
Oh.

866
00:49:25,681 --> 00:49:27,201
All those memories.

867
00:49:27,321 --> 00:49:29,201
The Matrix.

868
00:49:29,321 --> 00:49:30,921
The memories blew the Matrix.

869
00:49:32,041 --> 00:49:33,601
Oh, she's clever.

870
00:49:33,721 --> 00:49:34,881
I'm clever.

871
00:49:35,001 --> 00:49:36,721
We're all clever.

872
00:49:36,841 --> 00:49:37,841
All of us.

873
00:49:39,201 --> 00:49:40,521
However many that is.

874
00:49:40,641 --> 00:49:42,241
All right, then.

875
00:49:43,361 --> 00:49:45,041
Off we go. Ugh!

876
00:49:45,161 --> 00:49:47,721
No, there's something
I'm missing.

877
00:49:50,681 --> 00:49:53,401
The Master is creating
a new race of Cybermen

878
00:49:53,521 --> 00:49:55,001
using Time Lord bodies.

879
00:49:56,161 --> 00:49:58,481
An endlessly regenerating army.

880
00:49:58,601 --> 00:50:00,601
I have to stop him.

881
00:50:00,721 --> 00:50:01,921
Fast.

882
00:50:02,041 --> 00:50:03,961
You shouldn't be here.

883
00:50:04,081 --> 00:50:05,601
- No humans on Gallifrey.
- If it helps,

884
00:50:05,721 --> 00:50:07,641
- we have explosives.
- And a plan.

885
00:50:07,761 --> 00:50:10,161
The Cybership's parked up
in the middle of your hometown,

886
00:50:10,281 --> 00:50:11,201
it's ripe for blowing up.

887
00:50:11,321 --> 00:50:13,881
We're going to strategically
place bombs around the ship,

888
00:50:14,001 --> 00:50:15,841
including some close enough
to the core.

889
00:50:15,961 --> 00:50:17,321
Yes. Good.

890
00:50:17,441 --> 00:50:18,561
Do that.

891
00:50:18,681 --> 00:50:19,921
But it won't achieve
everything.

892
00:50:20,041 --> 00:50:23,201
A race of CyberMasters -
can't let them off this planet,

893
00:50:23,321 --> 00:50:24,401
have to be stopped.

894
00:50:24,521 --> 00:50:26,121
And your bombs
aren't going to do that.

895
00:50:26,241 --> 00:50:28,081
We need more!
But there isn't anything more.

896
00:50:28,201 --> 00:50:29,801
The Master's seen to that.

897
00:50:30,841 --> 00:50:33,561
The Master's seen
to everything.

898
00:50:33,681 --> 00:50:35,281
Are you all right, Doctor?

899
00:50:35,401 --> 00:50:36,521
(SIGHS)

900
00:50:37,641 --> 00:50:38,961
That's what's been bugging me.

901
00:50:40,281 --> 00:50:42,081
That's the thing
that he said to me.

902
00:50:42,201 --> 00:50:43,401
What thing? Who said?

903
00:50:43,521 --> 00:50:45,321
The half-converted Cyberman.

904
00:50:45,441 --> 00:50:47,561
The death of everything...

905
00:50:48,841 --> 00:50:50,561
...Is within me.

906
00:50:50,681 --> 00:50:53,321
That's what he said! Argh!

907
00:50:53,441 --> 00:50:55,241
But what did it mean?

908
00:50:55,361 --> 00:50:57,601
There is a myth around him.

909
00:50:57,721 --> 00:50:58,801
The Death Particle.

910
00:50:58,921 --> 00:51:01,841
The legend is -
he, it, whatever

911
00:51:01,961 --> 00:51:03,601
has a Particle
in a tiny chamber

912
00:51:03,721 --> 00:51:05,081
inside its chest.

913
00:51:05,201 --> 00:51:08,601
It will take out
all organic life on a planet.

914
00:51:08,721 --> 00:51:11,001
- That's grim.
- Or it's a solution.

915
00:51:11,121 --> 00:51:15,361
A timer on an explosive
to activate the Particle

916
00:51:15,481 --> 00:51:17,681
- and a clear evacuation plan.
- Only if you've got a way

917
00:51:17,801 --> 00:51:19,561
to get us off this planet
before it hits.

918
00:51:19,681 --> 00:51:21,881
You all good to set
those explosives?

919
00:51:22,001 --> 00:51:23,961
I'll deal with the rest.

920
00:51:24,081 --> 00:51:26,321
Meet in the corridor
below the carrier.

921
00:51:26,441 --> 00:51:28,201
Go on, then!

922
00:51:28,321 --> 00:51:31,041
Now, I need to get
a fix on the Master.

923
00:51:37,641 --> 00:51:39,041
Got him.

924
00:51:50,361 --> 00:51:51,441
(COMMS BEEPS)

925
00:51:51,561 --> 00:51:53,041
Found the activator core.

926
00:51:53,161 --> 00:51:54,321
If this one goes,

927
00:51:54,441 --> 00:51:57,521
it'll set off chain reactions
across the carrier.

928
00:51:57,641 --> 00:51:59,561
(EXPLOSIVES BUZZ)

929
00:52:03,841 --> 00:52:05,201
(BUZZES)

930
00:52:07,601 --> 00:52:08,641
We're set.

931
00:52:08,761 --> 00:52:10,481
(BUZZES)

932
00:52:10,601 --> 00:52:12,321
Sweet dreams, losers.

933
00:52:13,721 --> 00:52:16,401
(BUZZES)

934
00:52:16,521 --> 00:52:18,601
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

935
00:52:22,641 --> 00:52:26,041
DOCTOR: Where's the Master?
He should be here.

936
00:52:34,001 --> 00:52:35,721
(SONIC BUZZES)

937
00:52:35,841 --> 00:52:37,081
The Master?

938
00:52:37,201 --> 00:52:38,201
He did that?

939
00:52:39,441 --> 00:52:41,801
But the Death Particle
is still in place.

940
00:52:41,921 --> 00:52:43,641
Just smaller than before.

941
00:52:43,761 --> 00:52:46,041
If the Master did this...

942
00:52:46,161 --> 00:52:48,121
...what happened
to the Cyberium?

943
00:52:49,561 --> 00:52:50,601
(GASPS)

944
00:52:50,721 --> 00:52:53,001
You think I didn't feel you
connecting to me?

945
00:52:53,121 --> 00:52:55,201
(LAUGHS)

946
00:52:55,321 --> 00:52:56,921
Laid you a false trail.

947
00:52:58,081 --> 00:52:59,521
Left you a gift, though.

948
00:52:59,641 --> 00:53:02,601
You and me - Matrix Chamber.

949
00:53:02,721 --> 00:53:05,361
No-one else. One last time.

950
00:53:09,321 --> 00:53:10,281
Fine.

951
00:53:13,921 --> 00:53:15,561
I need to get you all
off Gallifrey.

952
00:53:15,681 --> 00:53:17,361
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS)

953
00:53:21,961 --> 00:53:23,881
(BUZZES)

954
00:53:26,521 --> 00:53:29,041
- (TICKING)
- Oh, dear.

955
00:53:29,161 --> 00:53:32,481
Sorry for the short notice.

956
00:53:32,601 --> 00:53:34,441
But it seems that
the main trigger device

957
00:53:34,561 --> 00:53:35,961
has a mind of its own

958
00:53:36,081 --> 00:53:37,601
and has set
all the others going.

959
00:53:37,721 --> 00:53:41,521
May I suggest a very fast
getting the hell off this ship?

960
00:53:41,641 --> 00:53:42,641
Run!

961
00:53:45,121 --> 00:53:48,081
Human life form located.
Delete.

962
00:53:50,081 --> 00:53:52,121
Execute all humans.

963
00:53:56,041 --> 00:53:58,161
All humans must be deleted.

964
00:54:04,921 --> 00:54:08,321
Humanity shall be eradicated.

965
00:54:08,441 --> 00:54:11,081
Incendiary devices identified.

966
00:54:17,681 --> 00:54:20,721
(SCREAMING)

967
00:54:23,361 --> 00:54:25,641
- Thanks for the warning.
- You're still alive,

968
00:54:25,761 --> 00:54:28,321
- aren't you?
- Everyone, through here.

969
00:54:28,441 --> 00:54:29,521
Come on.

970
00:54:31,161 --> 00:54:33,001
It's a TARDIS.

971
00:54:33,121 --> 00:54:34,881
It is a TARDIS, right?

972
00:54:35,001 --> 00:54:36,321
Looks like it.

973
00:54:36,441 --> 00:54:38,161
Sorry, what's happening now?

974
00:54:38,281 --> 00:54:39,601
This can take us all home.

975
00:54:41,921 --> 00:54:43,761
Don't touch. Still working.

976
00:54:43,881 --> 00:54:45,121
Any explosives left?

977
00:54:45,241 --> 00:54:46,721
One.

978
00:54:46,841 --> 00:54:47,961
Emergencies only.

979
00:54:48,081 --> 00:54:50,721
- Timer?
- Hand detonation only.

980
00:54:51,881 --> 00:54:53,641
Yeah. Course.

981
00:54:54,641 --> 00:54:56,001
I'll take it.

982
00:55:00,481 --> 00:55:02,241
So, come on, Doc,
what're you thinking?

983
00:55:05,281 --> 00:55:06,481
One option left.

984
00:55:14,681 --> 00:55:16,241
I have to use
the Death Particle

985
00:55:16,361 --> 00:55:18,081
on Gallifrey.

986
00:55:18,201 --> 00:55:19,321
On my home.

987
00:55:22,521 --> 00:55:25,521
On the Master
and his new breed of Cybermen.

988
00:55:25,641 --> 00:55:26,841
You sure you want to do that?

989
00:55:26,961 --> 00:55:28,441
I'm sure
I don't want to do that,

990
00:55:28,561 --> 00:55:29,921
but there's no alternative.

991
00:55:30,041 --> 00:55:32,281
If the Master and the Cybermen
get off this planet,

992
00:55:32,401 --> 00:55:33,881
they'll be unstoppable.

993
00:55:35,281 --> 00:55:38,561
I started this
with Shelley and the Cyberium,

994
00:55:38,681 --> 00:55:39,721
now I have to finish it.

995
00:55:42,521 --> 00:55:43,601
Alone.

996
00:55:43,721 --> 00:55:44,761
What?

997
00:55:46,281 --> 00:55:48,241
The TARDIS will take you
back to Earth.

998
00:55:48,361 --> 00:55:49,601
All of you.

999
00:55:49,721 --> 00:55:51,801
You can settle
in the 21st century.

1000
00:55:51,921 --> 00:55:54,881
- You're not serious.
- Deadly.

1001
00:55:55,001 --> 00:55:57,281
What about you?

1002
00:55:57,401 --> 00:55:59,241
You detonate that thing,
you'll die, too.

1003
00:56:01,361 --> 00:56:02,641
That's the way it has to be.

1004
00:56:06,481 --> 00:56:08,841
And I would do that
in a heartbeat

1005
00:56:08,961 --> 00:56:10,441
for this universe.

1006
00:56:16,001 --> 00:56:17,001
For you...

1007
00:56:19,121 --> 00:56:20,401
...my fam.

1008
00:56:24,641 --> 00:56:26,481
We're not letting you go.

1009
00:56:26,601 --> 00:56:28,601
- You're not doing this.
- Get off me, Yaz!

1010
00:56:33,961 --> 00:56:34,961
Please.

1011
00:56:40,921 --> 00:56:42,001
Yaz.

1012
00:56:43,321 --> 00:56:44,441
Come on.

1013
00:56:53,321 --> 00:56:54,441
Live great lives.

1014
00:57:32,081 --> 00:57:34,721
I definitely said no plus-ones.

1015
00:57:34,841 --> 00:57:36,641
Well... Oh!

1016
00:57:36,761 --> 00:57:39,001
Where I go, they go now.

1017
00:57:39,121 --> 00:57:40,761
Are you going to have them
shoot me?

1018
00:57:40,881 --> 00:57:41,961
No, Doctor.

1019
00:57:43,001 --> 00:57:44,161
As of now,

1020
00:57:44,281 --> 00:57:46,921
I wish my enemies
a long and healthy life,

1021
00:57:47,041 --> 00:57:50,321
so they may witness
my many triumphs,

1022
00:57:50,441 --> 00:57:52,761
because they will be legion.

1023
00:57:54,281 --> 00:57:55,761
You're looking peaky.

1024
00:57:55,881 --> 00:57:57,321
Oh, yeah!

1025
00:57:58,721 --> 00:58:01,961
The Cyberium lives in me now,
Doctor.

1026
00:58:04,081 --> 00:58:06,001
(CHUCKLES) Yes!

1027
00:58:06,121 --> 00:58:07,961
See...

1028
00:58:08,081 --> 00:58:09,321
(SHIVERS WITH EXCITEMENT)

1029
00:58:09,441 --> 00:58:11,881
I've been looking forward
to seeing your face about that.

1030
00:58:12,001 --> 00:58:14,721
I can feel it

1031
00:58:14,841 --> 00:58:17,001
flowing around in me -

1032
00:58:17,121 --> 00:58:20,721
the information, the strategy,

1033
00:58:20,841 --> 00:58:22,481
the...the consciousness.

1034
00:58:24,361 --> 00:58:25,641
It's a beautiful thing.

1035
00:58:27,801 --> 00:58:29,681
I mean, look at us.

1036
00:58:30,921 --> 00:58:32,641
I have broken you

1037
00:58:32,761 --> 00:58:35,201
and created a new race.

1038
00:58:35,321 --> 00:58:36,321
And now...

1039
00:58:37,681 --> 00:58:39,561
Well, now I shall conquer...

1040
00:58:40,801 --> 00:58:42,361
...everything.

1041
00:58:43,601 --> 00:58:44,921
Oh!

1042
00:58:45,041 --> 00:58:47,921
You think you've broken me?

1043
00:58:49,721 --> 00:58:52,001
You'll have to try
harder than that.

1044
00:58:53,761 --> 00:58:55,921
You've given me a gift.

1045
00:58:58,841 --> 00:59:00,241
Of myself.

1046
00:59:04,681 --> 00:59:07,001
You think
that could destroy me?

1047
00:59:07,121 --> 00:59:08,921
You think
that makes me lesser?

1048
00:59:10,681 --> 00:59:13,201
It makes me more.

1049
00:59:13,321 --> 00:59:17,641
I contain multitudes more
than I ever thought or knew.

1050
00:59:17,761 --> 00:59:19,121
You want me to be scared of it

1051
00:59:19,241 --> 00:59:21,321
because you're scared
of everything.

1052
00:59:22,441 --> 00:59:25,161
But I am so much more than you.

1053
00:59:29,001 --> 00:59:30,641
Wow.

1054
00:59:30,761 --> 00:59:32,441
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

1055
00:59:37,001 --> 00:59:38,721
So, why are we here?

1056
00:59:43,161 --> 00:59:47,241
(GASPS) Oh, good, very good.

1057
00:59:47,361 --> 00:59:49,041
That's why I left it for you.

1058
00:59:49,161 --> 00:59:50,561
Wondered if you would...

1059
00:59:54,921 --> 00:59:56,801
...take out me.

1060
00:59:56,921 --> 00:59:59,361
Take out these life forms.

1061
00:59:59,481 --> 01:00:02,041
All those bodies
still in the vaults.

1062
01:00:02,161 --> 01:00:06,241
Every organic cellular
life form on this planet...

1063
01:00:06,361 --> 01:00:07,521
...forever.

1064
01:00:08,961 --> 01:00:10,641
And yourself.

1065
01:00:13,281 --> 01:00:14,481
Do that, would you?

1066
01:00:16,601 --> 01:00:17,761
Yes.

1067
01:00:18,881 --> 01:00:20,041
This time...

1068
01:00:21,041 --> 01:00:22,241
...yes.

1069
01:00:22,361 --> 01:00:23,761
Go on, then.

1070
01:00:25,921 --> 01:00:29,321
You were the start of
all of this, now finish it.

1071
01:00:29,441 --> 01:00:31,401
Come on, come on.

1072
01:00:31,521 --> 01:00:32,841
Come on!

1073
01:00:32,961 --> 01:00:35,441
Come on, come on!

1074
01:00:35,561 --> 01:00:37,641
What have you got left anyway?

1075
01:00:37,761 --> 01:00:40,081
You don't even know
your own life.

1076
01:00:40,201 --> 01:00:43,161
Look how low
I have brought you.

1077
01:00:45,161 --> 01:00:47,441
I have won, Doctor.

1078
01:00:47,561 --> 01:00:51,481
You may have made me,
but I have destroyed you.

1079
01:00:54,201 --> 01:00:56,041
Become death.

1080
01:00:58,681 --> 01:01:00,441
Become me.

1081
01:01:02,401 --> 01:01:03,961
Come on.

1082
01:01:04,081 --> 01:01:05,801
Come on, come on.

1083
01:01:15,401 --> 01:01:17,681
For just a moment there,
I thought maybe.

1084
01:01:18,801 --> 01:01:21,161
Argh! (EXHALES DISMISSIVELY)

1085
01:01:21,281 --> 01:01:23,521
Oh, Doctor.

1086
01:01:23,641 --> 01:01:26,201
The universe will suffer
for your weakness,

1087
01:01:26,321 --> 01:01:27,481
I'lLl make sure of it.

1088
01:01:27,601 --> 01:01:29,201
KO SHARMUS: Not if
I have anything to do with it.

1089
01:01:30,601 --> 01:01:32,161
Excuse me?

1090
01:01:32,281 --> 01:01:33,561
No gate-crashers.

1091
01:01:33,681 --> 01:01:35,721
You can't still be here,
I set the controls!

1092
01:01:35,841 --> 01:01:36,801
I followed you out.

1093
01:01:36,921 --> 01:01:37,921
They tried to stop me,

1094
01:01:38,041 --> 01:01:41,401
but I wanted to be sure
that these things are gone.

1095
01:01:41,521 --> 01:01:44,241
- And now I can be.
- No.

1096
01:01:44,361 --> 01:01:45,441
(CHUCKLES)

1097
01:01:45,561 --> 01:01:47,841
You didn't start this. I did!

1098
01:01:47,961 --> 01:01:51,081
I was part of a resistance unit
that sent the Cyberium

1099
01:01:51,201 --> 01:01:52,401
back through time and space.

1100
01:01:52,521 --> 01:01:54,921
Though, obviously, we didn't
send it back far enough.

1101
01:01:56,281 --> 01:01:59,161
So, this is my penance.

1102
01:01:59,281 --> 01:02:02,201
Mine to finish.

1103
01:02:04,561 --> 01:02:06,681
My journey ends here.

1104
01:02:08,201 --> 01:02:10,641
But the universe
still needs you.

1105
01:02:12,241 --> 01:02:14,441
So, I suggest you run.

1106
01:02:14,561 --> 01:02:16,761
- But...
- Run, Doctor!

1107
01:02:18,041 --> 01:02:19,641
MASTER: Don't you dare.

1108
01:02:20,681 --> 01:02:22,161
Doctor!

1109
01:02:22,281 --> 01:02:24,761
Still feeling confident?

1110
01:02:27,801 --> 01:02:28,801
(SONIC BUZZES)

1111
01:02:28,921 --> 01:02:30,001
(WHIRRING)

1112
01:02:31,881 --> 01:02:33,441
(TARDIS POWERS UP)

1113
01:02:35,441 --> 01:02:36,921
Kill him.

1114
01:02:37,041 --> 01:02:38,641
Killed you first.

1115
01:02:40,641 --> 01:02:42,481
(GROANS)

1116
01:02:44,041 --> 01:02:46,521
MASTER: All of you,
through here - now!

1117
01:02:56,481 --> 01:02:59,961
(THRUMS)

1118
01:03:07,681 --> 01:03:09,201
This is Earth.

1119
01:03:13,081 --> 01:03:14,441
(EXHALES)

1120
01:03:16,241 --> 01:03:17,521
We're on Earth.

1121
01:03:17,641 --> 01:03:19,521
We're home.

1122
01:03:21,281 --> 01:03:23,481
She got us home.

1123
01:03:29,441 --> 01:03:30,681
But what happens to her?

1124
01:03:37,641 --> 01:03:39,321
Oh, yeah, nice.

1125
01:03:39,441 --> 01:03:41,081
Good chameleon circuit.

1126
01:03:41,201 --> 01:03:43,241
I'm going to have to
leave you there, though.

1127
01:03:46,761 --> 01:03:49,001
I can think of worse places
to spend eternity.

1128
01:03:54,401 --> 01:03:56,361
(POWERS UP)

1129
01:03:56,481 --> 01:03:57,961
Hello, mate.

1130
01:03:58,081 --> 01:04:01,081
(TARDIS BEEPS)

1131
01:04:03,161 --> 01:04:04,641
Thanks.

1132
01:04:04,761 --> 01:04:05,841
Home sweet home.

1133
01:04:05,961 --> 01:04:07,881
(TARDIS WARBLES)

1134
01:04:08,001 --> 01:04:09,441
We got a lift back another way.

1135
01:04:09,561 --> 01:04:12,241
- (TARDIS BEEPS)
- Don't get jealous.

1136
01:04:12,361 --> 01:04:13,401
I'll pick them up now.

1137
01:04:16,121 --> 01:04:17,521
Maybe just need a moment.

1138
01:04:20,161 --> 01:04:22,041
(TARDIS BEEPS)

1139
01:04:31,161 --> 01:04:33,041
(ALARM BLARES)

1140
01:04:35,561 --> 01:04:36,521
What?

1141
01:04:36,641 --> 01:04:38,681
Judoon Cold Case Unit.

1142
01:04:38,801 --> 01:04:40,561
Fugitive - the Doctor.

1143
01:04:40,681 --> 01:04:43,321
Sentence -
whole of life imprisonment,

1144
01:04:43,441 --> 01:04:45,681
maximum security facility.

1145
01:04:50,121 --> 01:04:51,641
What?

1146
01:04:59,321 --> 01:05:00,921
What?!

